# LIFETIME Component System

## Visual Standard

Every section must look like it belongs to a premium clinical-editorial brand.
References: ag1.com (spacing), withings.com (clinical clarity), ritual.com (CTA proportion).

A result that technically follows the rules but feels generic is a FAILED result.

## MANDATORY: Before building any section

1. Open `_examples/README.md`
2. Find the closest approved example in `_examples/sections/`
3. Read its `{% comment %}` block — it documents every decision
4. Read its CSS — every non-obvious choice is explained
5. Match token usage exactly. Adapt content. Keep the discipline.

The visual target for all PDP work is `_examples/pdp-reference.html`.
Open it before building any PDP section.

## Section Build Process (§12)

Before writing any code, answer these:

| Decision | Required answer |
|---|---|
| Surface | Which surface token? |
| Dominant element | What does the eye land on first? |
| Heading size | `--text-h1` major / `--text-h2` supporting |
| Content pattern | card-info / card-review / stat-callout / quote-block / benefit-surface |
| CTA | Which variant and label? Or: none. |
| What to remove | Apply subtraction rules. List what and why. |
| Quality move | One decision that makes this feel premium, not generic. |

## Section Surface Rhythm

Default alternating: white → warm → white → warm
Dark sections are intentional breaks. Max 1–2 per page.

| Context | Token |
|---|---|
| Default | `--color-surface-primary` |
| Alternating | `--color-surface-secondary` |
| Emphasis / quote | `--color-surface-dark` |
| Benefit areas | `--color-surface-benefit` |

## Component Specs

### Button
- Height: 48px, padding: 14px 32px, radius: `--radius-full`
- `cta` → dark bg, white text (revenue actions)
- `outline` → transparent, dark text, currentColor border
- `outline-inverted` → on dark surfaces: white border + white text
- Font: `--font-body`, `--text-body-sm`, `--weight-semibold`

### Card Info (benefits, features, steps)
- White bg, `--radius-md`, padding `--space-5`
- Border: `1px solid var(--color-border-default)` on white sections
- Shadow: `--shadow-sm` on white bg only
- Icon: 48px container, `--color-surface-benefit` bg, `--color-teal-dark` icon
- Title: `--font-heading`, `--text-section`, bold
- Description: `--font-body`, `--text-body`, secondary color

### Card Review
- White bg, `--radius-md`, padding `--space-5`
- Border: `1px solid var(--color-border-default)`
- Stars: `--color-star`
- Verified badge: `--color-success`, transparent bg, inline with icon
- Date: `--text-micro`, muted

### Stat Callout
- Number: `--font-heading`, `--text-stat`, bold, white on dark
- Suffix: `--font-heading`, `--text-h3`, bold, `--color-teal-dark`
- Label: `--font-body`, `--text-body-sm`, `--color-text-on-dark-muted`

### Section Header
- Centered, max-width 640px
- Label: `--text-micro`, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.1em, muted
- Title: `--font-heading`, `--text-h1` or `--text-h2`, bold
- Description: `--font-body`, `--text-body-lg`, secondary

### Trust Strip (PDP)
- Pills with border: `1px solid var(--color-border-default)`, `--radius-full`
- Icon 15px + label `--text-body-sm`
- Wrap to second line (no horizontal scroll)

### Benefit Surface
- Background: `--color-surface-benefit` (#E6F4F1)
- Border: `1px solid rgba(94,171,161,0.18)`
- Radius: `--radius-lg`
- Checkmarks: `--color-teal-dark` (NOT green)

## Typography Rules

- Headings (`≥ --text-h3`): always `--font-heading`
- Body, labels, badges: always `--font-body`
- Never body text in Helvetica
- Never headings in Lato
- Max 3 type sizes per section (2 preferred)
- Size contrast between heading and body must be clearly visible at a glance

## Visual Weight Rules

- Every section has exactly ONE dominant element
- Supporting elements must be visually subordinate
- CTA buttons must have `--space-7` minimum above them
- On dark surfaces: reduce element count by one vs. equivalent light section

## Subtraction Rules (apply before finalizing)

Remove:
- decorative dividers not needed for structure
- icons that duplicate what text already says
- labels if the heading already makes context clear
- secondary CTAs if primary CTA covers the decision
- body text that repeats what sub-components already say

## Anti-Patterns — Never Do These

- Hardcoded hex, px, or font names in CSS
- `#000000` as background
- Multiple CTAs fighting in same viewport
- Shadow to compensate for weak hierarchy
- Generic "UI kit" cards that could be any health brand
- Shrinking headings because layout is poorly composed
- Tight spacing — air looks premium, tight looks cheap

## Final Quality Gate

Before outputting code, ask:
1. Does this look premium enough for LIFETIME?
2. Does this feel designed, not assembled?
3. If stripped of copy, would hierarchy still look convincing?
4. Is there anything here that exists only because it was easy to build?

If any answer is no — refine before output.
